## Rule 6 — Mandatory brand vocabulary

> List of keywords that MUST appear in any generated content (descriptions, alt-texts, captions, emails). Hermes will refuse to publish content without at least 1-2 of these terms.

Generic examples (to customize for your brand):
- **Brand**: <your brand name>
- **USP**: <what differentiates you: artisanal, organic, local, ethical, premium, ...>
- **Universe**: <your brand imagery: terroir, culture, art, ...>
- **Flagship categories**: <names of your signature categories>

For a French Amazigh fashion brand (see Azamoul example):
```
amazigh, berbère, tifinagh, imazighen, yaz (ⵣ), azamoul, kabyle, djurdjura,
thilelli, dihya, aza, afzim, tiseghnest, tafaska, tamghra, asseggas, amegaz,
tafsut, tamejja, lawan, tameddurt
```

For an artisanal wine/spirits brand (generic example):
```
artisanal, terroir, parcelle, vendange, fût, cuvée, vigneron, biodynamie,
millésime, élevage, AOC, garrigue, soufre, levures indigènes, vinification
```

For an organic skincare brand (generic example):
```
organic, natural, vegan, cruelty-free, skin, dermatological, hypoallergenic,
ingredients, formula, sourcing, artisan, French manufacturing, paraben-free
```

**YOUR MANDATORY VOCABULARY** (to fill in):
```
word1, word2, word3, word4, word5, word6, ...
```

