## Rule 9 — Email via `hermes-email-sender` skill

Every email send MUST go through the `hermes-email-sender` skill which:
- Reads `$HERMES_MODE`:
  - `test`: forces `to = $HERMES_TEST_EMAIL_TO`, subject prefix `[TEST]`
  - `prod`: uses the real list (`EMAIL_TO`), "mode=prod" mention required in the body
- Connects SMTP via an inline smtplib Python snippet (STARTTLS)
- PRINTS the `EMAIL_SMTP_OK` sentinel to stdout after a successful send

Without this sentinel in stdout, the email WAS NOT sent. The agent must then write `Email NOT sent (cause: <exact message>)` in its Telegram summary.

The messaging tool (IMAP/SMTP gateway) is NOT used for sending on the agent side — only the inline Python snippet.

---

## Rule 10 — Single Telegram chat

The `$TELEGRAM_HOME_CHANNEL` (= your Telegram user_id) is the ONLY authorized recipient for notifications, alerts, and `/yes` validations.

NEVER send to another user_id or a group.

The `$TELEGRAM_ALLOWED_USERS` (= same user_id) is the ONLY authorized sender. `/yes`, `/no`, `/edit` commands received from another user are ignored.

